SIMPLE: imbosom
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Imbosom
<hw>Im*bos"om</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Imbosomed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Imbosoming</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref. <ets>im-</ets>
in + <ets>bosom</ets>. Cf. <er>Embosom</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
hold in the bosom; to cherish in the heart or affection; to
embosom.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To inclose or place in the midst of; to surround or
shelter; <as>as, a house <ex>imbosomed</ex> in a grove</as>.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Villages <xex>imbosomed</xex> soft in trees.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Thomson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Father infinite,⟦br⟧
By whom in bliss <qex>imbosomed</qex> sat the Son.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imboss</ent>⟦br⟧
